This paper focuses on improving the usefulness of code review comments through the analysis of textual features and developer experience. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the textual characteristics of the comments, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) categories. The paper also discusses the impact of reviewer experience on comment usefulness, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) categories.
